## [FAIL] MEDIUM — M2: Conditional rendering of `LeadBlock` on grid-cover not specified

**What the spec says:** A2: "Lead rendert auf Slide 1 (kind: "grid") IF `meta.lead` non-empty." The Files-to-Change JSX for the grid-cover branch shows `<LeadBlock lead={...} marginTop={TITLE_TO_LEAD_GAP_GRID_COVER} centered />` without a conditional wrapper.

**What a developer implements:** Two interpretations: (a) Unconditionally render `<LeadBlock lead={meta.lead} .../>` even when empty — Satori renders an empty div with `TITLE_TO_LEAD_GAP_GRID_COVER` margin (32px) wasted on top. (b) `{meta.lead && <LeadBlock .../>}` — conditional render, but then what happens to `LEAD_TO_GRID_GAP_GRID_COVER` spacing (see C1)?

**Fix required:** Add the conditional guard explicitly to the JSX snippet: `{slide.meta.lead && <LeadBlock lead={slide.meta.lead} ... />}`. This also forces the developer to handle the spacing when Lead is absent (linking to C1 resolution).

