## [FAIL] MEDIUM — M3: grid-path forEach `leadOnSlide` change in `splitAgendaIntoSlides` has no code snippet

**What the spec says:** A2 states "Both `splitAgendaIntoSlides` AND `buildManualSlides` müssen `leadOnSlide: false` für ALL text-slides setzen wenn `hasGrid === true`." Files-to-Change entry (b) for `instagram-post.ts` restates this.

**What the spec omits:** No VORHER/NACHHER code snippet for the grid-path forEach in `splitAgendaIntoSlides` (currently at line 477-483: `leadOnSlide: i === 0 && Boolean(lead)`). The only code snippets in A3b are for the no-grid push and for `buildManualSlides`. A developer focused on the code snippets might change only the no-grid push (A3b) and the manual-path forEach, missing the auto-path grid-path forEach entirely.

**Fix required:** Add VORHER/NACHHER snippet for the auto-path grid-path forEach. VORHER: `leadOnSlide: i === 0 && Boolean(lead)`. NACHHER: `leadOnSlide: false` (or omit the property — it's falsy by default).

